    <h1>{`Trigger and Resolve Alerts with Email Management Rules`}</h1>
    <p>{`By default, PagerDuty opens a new incident every time an email is received at the integration address of an `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "https://www.pagerduty.com/docs/guides/email-integration-guide/"
      }}>{`email integration`}</a>{`. Depending on how your monitoring tool works, this behavior might not be desirable.`}</p>
    <p>{`The first line of defense in limiting unnecessary noise in email integrations are `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "#section-limit-noise-with-email-integration-filters"
      }}>{`email filters`}</a>{`. These filters select which of your inbound events will become events on your service, and which events will be discarded. `}</p>
    <p>{`Once an event is accepted by your email filters, email management rules may be used to determine the way accepted events will behave. PagerDuty's email management feature allows you to automatically resolve incidents from email integrations by creating custom rules to parse messages and specify how they should be handled.`}</p>
    <ul>
      <li parentName="ul"><a parentName="li" {...{
